### Order → Subscription end-to-end driver
#
# Drives the full flow against a locally-running server:
#   customer → product (subscription price) → payment method → order → complete → verify
#
# Auth is via an org-scoped API key sent as `x-api-key`. The key already binds
# to an org, so there is no org-creation step — every call is scoped to that org.
#
# Requires the api-key authenticator wired into internal/config/app.go (done) and
# API_KEY_PEPPER set to the same value used when the key was minted.
#
# Usage:
#   - VS Code REST Client / JetBrains HTTP Client: run each `###` block top-to-bottom.
#   - The `# @name` tags let later requests reference earlier responses
#     (e.g. {{createCustomer.response.body.$.id}}), so run them in order.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:10081
@apiKey = sk_3Ed55ejAEXHr0fAWH1iHbwlakVB_4gAR1nAMXxLfColVx5yFhc7VnXyKBvlKQSF6oddlXiw

### 1. Create a customer (with a billing address — required to attach a payment method)
# @name createCustomer
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/customers
x-api-key: {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "subtest+{{$timestamp}}@example.com",
  "first_name": "Sub",
  "last_name": "Tester",
  "billing_address": {
    "first_name": "Sub",
    "last_name": "Tester",
    "line1": "1 Test Street",
    "city": "Cape Town",
    "postal_code": "8001",
    "country": "ZA"
  }
}

### 2. Create a product with a monthly subscription price
# @name createProduct
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/products
x-api-key: {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Test Subscription Plan",
  "description": "Monthly plan used to verify the order→subscription flow",
  "variants": [
    {
      "name": "Standard",
      "prices": [
        {
          "label": "Standard Monthly",
          "category": "subscription",
          "scheme": "fixed",
          "currency": "USD",
          "unit_price": 5000,
          "billing_interval": "month",
          "billing_interval_qty": 1
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}

### Capture ids from the product response
@productId = {{createProduct.response.body.$.id}}
@priceId = {{createProduct.response.body.$.variants[0].prices[0].id}}
@customerId = {{createCustomer.response.body.$.id}}

### 3. Attach a payment method to the customer (token is a dummy — no gateway call)
# @name createPaymentMethod
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/customers/{{customerId}}/payment-methods
x-api-key: {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "psp": "paystack",
  "name": "Test Card",
  "type": "card",
  "token": "tok_test_dummy_{{$timestamp}}",
  "is_default": true
}

### Capture the payment method id
@paymentMethodId = {{createPaymentMethod.response.body.$.id}}

### 4. Create an order with a direct cart (no session → no live PSP charge)
# @name createOrder
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/orders
x-api-key: {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "customer": {
    "id": "{{customerId}}"
  },
  "payment_method_id": "{{paymentMethodId}}",
  "psp_id": "paystack",
  "cart": {
    "currency": "USD",
    "items": [
      {
        "product_id": "{{productId}}",
        "price_id": "{{priceId}}",
        "quantity": 1
      }
    ]
  }
}

### Capture the order id
@orderId = {{createOrder.response.body.$.order.id}}

### 5. Complete the order — records first payment, activates subscription, starts workflow
# @name completeOrder
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/orders/{{orderId}}/complete
x-api-key: {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "payment_method_id": "{{paymentMethodId}}",
  "payment": {
    "psp_id": "paystack",
    "reference": "ref_test_{{$timestamp}}",
    "amount": 5000,
    "currency": "USD"
  }
}

### 6. Verify — the order's subscription(s) should now be `active`
# @name listOrderSubscriptions
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/orders/{{orderId}}/subscriptions
x-api-key: {{apiKey}}

### (optional) Inspect the subscription directly
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/subscriptions
x-api-key: {{apiKey}}
